text:
The javadoc for Driver.reset() states that this method "Resets the Driver so it 
can be reused. Property and element mappings are reset to defaults. The output 
stream is cleared. The renderer is cleared." however, it does not do this.

The source in fop-0.18.0 for this method is as follows:

    public synchronized void reset() 
    {
	_areaTree = null;
	_treeBuilder.reset();
    }

This method also must include "_renderer = null;" since the (PDFRenderer, at 
least) maintains the previously built document, and not re-instatiating it 
results in the new document being added to the tail of the old document, and run
() doesn't create a new renderer if the class variable _renderer is non-null.

Workaround:
     execute Driver.setRenderer(null) prior to Driver.run() when re-using a 
Driver.
